A crane at a Manhattan construction site collapsed, killing at least four people and injuring many.
Residents had complained about illegal construction practices.
The tragedy occurred as workers were extending the crane to start work on a new level.
Rescue efforts continued through the night, with several people still missing.
The devastating event left a community in shock and mourning.
The collapse raised concerns about crane safety in the city, prompting investigations into the cause of the accident.
The incident highlighted the dangers of construction work in urban areas.
